Awesome and smoothe!   Due to Covid, all bases were covered!

Unfortunately some fans weren’t doing a good job of keeping their mask on while they were in their seats. The ushers would remind them repeatedly but the fans who were pulling it down would end up pulling it down again. When they wanted to yell loudly they pulled it down so they could project more and I felt a little unsafe because of it. At one point the security came and took one guy away who kept breaking the rules, but then he was allowed to come back 5 minutes later and at the end of the game broke the rules some more. I think the ushers need to learn how to be more strict about it and there needs to be more security personnel so they can throw people out who continually break the rules. Then hopefully the others will realize you are serious about it and won’t pull their masks down. Be more like Disneyland. They are on you like white on rice if your mask comes down below your nose or if you take it down and aren’t actively drinking or eating. People took advantage of that rule and kept their mask down while they were holding their drink even if they weren’t actively drinking.
Too many people going out the same exits at the end of the game and down the same escalators. Need to space it out. Need to kick fans out who don’t follow mask rule.
The cleaning of handrails and things seemed very good and ticketless entry was awesome.
Be stricter on fans keeping masks off or under their nose more, especially while not actively drinking or eating. Security follow through and remove people.

Cleaning handrails and watching the fans. I think it was their first game and they didn’t realize how hard it would be to keep people to keep their masks up. It takes consistent effort the whole game.
More security personnel are needed to remove fans that don’t follow the rules. I feel like every 2 or 3 sections needs their own dedicated security people.
Cleanliness the seating arrangement with the tape was nice.
The new food app seemed cool, I just didn’t use it because I didn’t want to take my mask off indoors.

It was so fun to attend an event! I love the changes, ordering on our phone, NO SMOKING, new payment system. I know the plan was last minute, so not all options were available. I look forward to drinking gluten-free beer and cider. I hope individual items in the app can be labeled vegan and/or gluten-free, etc.

I saw a staff member in the bathroom washing her face, a little odd, but maybe okay. I saw people eating and drinking in undersigned areas, some wearing a bandana or gaiter or with their nose out. I would love for staff to ask these folx to modify their behavior.
I like how much I saw cleaning happen. Having the seats bound was a great idea.
Subtitles on the big screen. I frequently can’t hear or understand the announcer.
I liked the taped anthem and questions with Melo.
Add to menu items tags for vegan, gluten-free, etc. Deliver food and drinks to seats.
More vegan and gluten-free options with clear labels.
